    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      207.97,
      514.12,
      262.68
    ],
    "text": "On 11 May 2026, officers from the Police Special Task Force Akmeemana Camp conducted a raid on a hotel in the Dodanduwa area within the Hikkaduwa Police Division and arrested 55 foreign nationals along with the hotel owner who allegedly provided accommodation facilities.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      277.24,
      478.34,
      304.32
    ],
    "text": "The arrested foreign nationals comprise 35 Indian nationals and 20 Nepalese nationals, suspected of offences under the Computer Crimes Act.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      318.76,
      521.62,
      359.64
    ],
    "text": "During the operation, officers also seized 25 computers, 119 mobile phones, Rs. 750,000 in cash, a car, and a jeep, which were produced before the Hikkaduwa Police Station.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      374.2,
      523.28,
      401.28
    ],
    "text": "The suspects are between 20 and 48 years of age, and the hotel owner is a 43-year-old resident of Dodanduwa.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.42,
      415.74,
      444.46,
      429.02
    ],
    "text": "Further investigations are being carried out by the Hikkaduwa Police.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
